question_text:
The measure of an angle is 33°. What is the measure of its complementary angle?
___°
solution:
Since the angles are complementary, their measures must add to 90°. Set up an equation and solve for n.
$33°+n=90°$
Subtract 33° from both sides:
$n=90°-33°$
$n=57°$
The measure of the complementary angle is 57°.
